</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-thumbnail"><div class="field-content imageleft">  <a href="/blog/interviews/taming-disorder-conversation-megha-sood-mbizo-chirasha" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/blog_thumbnail/public/Sood_anchor.jpg?itok=7s22UgTe" width="100" height="75" alt="Megha Sood with the cover to her book Language of the Wound Is Love" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-blog-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><h4 class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/interviews/taming-disorder-conversation-megha-sood-mbizo-chirasha">Taming the Disorder: A Conversation with Megha Sood</a>
</h4></div><div><div class="blog-summary">Megha Sood is an award-winning Asian American author, poet, editor, curator, and literary activist from New Jersey. She is the author of four poetry…
</div></div><span class="views-field views-field-field-date"><span class="field-content date-display-single">October 15, 2025
</span></span>|<span><span class="field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/mbizo-chirasha" hreflang="en">Mbizo Chirasha</a>
